<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"754\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-754x1024.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-280\" srcset=\"https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-754x1024.jpeg 754w, https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-221x300.jpeg 221w, https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-768x1043.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-1131x1536.jpeg 1131w, https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM.jpeg 1178w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 754px) 100vw, 754px\" \/><figcaption>acrylic on canvas, 2019<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"769\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-1-769x1024.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-279\" srcset=\"https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-1-769x1024.jpeg 769w, https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-1-225x300.jpeg 225w, https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-1-768x1022.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-1-1154x1536.jpeg 1154w, https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-09-at-3.28.06-PM-1.jpeg 1202w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 769px) 100vw, 769px\" \/><figcaption>pen &amp; ink on transparent paper, 2022<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The artwork is accompanied with texts directly from each woman* in the artwork.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2019 series, which questions the influence of time and society on women and their decision-making options, emerged from the 30th anniversary of Ban Ying e.V. (www.ban-ying.de) under the title: <strong>Nit in Transit &#8211; Cecile in Exile &#8211; Dora in Diaspora<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2022 series is about the question:<br><strong>\u201cWhat have you done that made you realize that you are an awesome and powerful woman<em>?\u201d <\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The women in this series came from Southeast Asia and are part of the advocacy work of the project by <a href=\"https:\/\/www.gaatw.org\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.gaatw.org\">Global Alliance Against Traffic in Women<\/a> (GAATW) and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ban-ying.de\/\">Ban Ying e.V.<\/a> about\/for inclusive re-\/integration of women in their home countries and in Germany. In both series are all women migrants.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Krisanta Caguioa-M\u00f6nnich<\/strong> is a language and cultural mediator in the women organization Ban Ying e.V.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Through her close contact with the residents of the shelter and the clients of the counseling center, she was inspired to make the women* through her art as reminders, capture part of their story and tell it to the public.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Sponsored by University of the Philippines Alumni Association in Germany e.V.<\/em><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Exhibition Opening 18 June 2022, 16:00 \u2013 19:00 Galerie im Stadtteilzentrum PrenzlauerbergFehrbelliner Stra\u00dfe 9210119&nbsp;Berlin Free entrance!16:00-16:30 &#8211; Registrationfrom 16:30 &#8211; Music performance: Isa Tabasuares17:00 &#8211; Brief introduction of artworks17:30 &#8211; Finger food and drinks18:00 &#8211; Poetry reading: Bernice Delos Reyes19:00 &#8211; End of event The exhibition consists of two &#8220;portrait&#8221; series: The artwork is accompanied&hellip;&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/upaagermany.org\/me-in-the-midst-of-changing-times